      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HES A TERROR (4) has been knocking on the door for a while and went close again last week when he worked but fought on to go under by 2.8m at this circuit, his third runner-up result on the trot. Draws a couple of spots lower so could break through. BURTON (8) made it two wins from his last four appearances at this venue when he came from this barrier to beat HES A TERROR in a brave performance last week. Could do it again. CRIMSON ROCK NZ (1) scored from wider at Temora last week, giving her two wins and two seconds from her last five starts. Draws to play a role again. MAJOR HAYLEY (9) should be at her peak fitness now. Draws for a trail and has the hoof on the till after placing in two of her last three starts.",
